8 PROPOSED OVERSIGHT COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to behavioral health; defining terms;
directing the Medicaid program to expand services;
10 providing scope of practice for behavioral health
clinical interns; requiring behavioral health interns
11 to comply with all administrative requirements;
providing for codification; and providing an
12 effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 15-101 of Title 43A, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 As used in this section:
20 1. "Behavioral health clinical intern" means a graduate student
21 enrolled in a nationally accredited clinical training program that
22 meets minimum credentials for service provided or code billed;
23 2. "Clinical training program" means programs of study that are
24 nationally accredited master's or doctoral programs preparing
Req. No. 16368 Page 1

1 stud ents for the licensed marriage and family therapist (LMFT),
2 licensed professional counselor (LPC), licensed clinical social
3 worker (LCSW), licensed alcohol and drug counselor (LADC), or
4 psychologist state licensures to practice;
5 3. "Licensed behavioral health provider" means a behavioral
6 health professional that is a licensed professional counselor (LPC),
7 licensed family and marital therapist (LFMT), licensed behavioral
8 practitioner (LBP), licensed clinical social worker (LCSW), licensed
9 alcohol and drug counselor (LADC), or licensed psychologist; and
10 4. "Nationally accredited program" means that the training
11 program has met all training standards to hold an active
12 accreditation aligned with the discipline of study, including but
13 not limited to, the Commission on Accreditation for Marriage and
14 Family Therapy Education (COAMFTE), the Council for Accreditation of
15 Counseling and Related Educational Programs (CACREP), the Council on
16 Social Work Education (CSWE), or the American Psychological
17 Association (APA).
18 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 15-102 of Title 43A, unless
20 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 The Oklahoma Medicaid Plan administrator shall expand services
22 by adding a provider code for master's and doctoral level behavioral
23 health clinical interns.
24
Req. No. 16368 Page 2

1 Behavioral health clinical intern providers shall only provide
2 services billable through clinical sites that are accredited in good
3 standing with behavioral health services site accreditations such
4 as: the Commission on Accreditation of Rehabilitation Facilities
5 (CARF), The Joint Commission, the American Society of Addiction
6 Medicine (ASAM) Level of Care Certification, program certification
7 through the Oklahoma Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse
8 Services, the Council on Accreditation (COA) or other national
9 behavioral health service site accrediting body.
10 Behavioral health clinical interns may provide services within
11 their clinical scope of practice under the on-site supervision of a
12 licensed behavioral health provider. On-site supervisors may only
13 supervise six (6) or fewer behavioral health clinical interns at any
14 time.
15 Behavioral health clinical interns shall comply with all
16 registration, training, documentation, and protocols required of
17 other behavioral health providers in the Oklahoma Medicaid plan.
18 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
